"Education information: Beijing reduces the proportion of talented students admitted to junior high school in 2016 - Xinhua News Agency."
"On the 21st and 22nd, the admission examination for talented students in Beijing junior high schools will be organized and implemented by the district education committees."
"This year, all districts in Beijing have reduced the proportion of talented student admissions, making the competition for talented students even more intense."
"For example, in Dongcheng District, the overall proportion of talented students admitted to junior high school from elementary school in the district this year will not exceed 5% of the district's total enrollment plan, with a planned enrollment of 380 students, and the proportion of admitted students will not exceed 10% of the school's enrollment plan."
"All students with athletic, artistic, or technological talents who register online are eligible to participate in the talented student admission examination."
"To make it convenient for students to participate in the examination nearby, Dongcheng District continues last year's examination arrangement and sets 1-2 examination venues in each school district, for a total of 13 examination venues."
"The examination venues are divided into examination rooms according to the examination district, and the examination periods are divided by hours. On the day of the examination, students will enter the examination venue at different periods according to their examination district and take the examination in different examination rooms."
"On May 23, the list of students who passed the examination will be publicly displayed on the website of the district education admission examination center, and students can check the examination results online."